      <div class="topic">
        <div class="about_detail-box">
          <h3 class="text-uppercase">
            About Me
          </h3>
          <p>
            I am a researcher at SandboxAQ, CA, USA, located in Germany. Before I have been
            affiliated to the Technische Universität (TU) Darmstadt as a post doctoral
            researcher in the cryptoplexity group led by Marc Fischlin. Until early 2022,
            I have been affiliated the Institute for Quantum Computing (IQC) as a post
            doctoral fellow at the Department of Combinatorics & Optimization at the
            University of Waterloo (UW) in Waterloo, Ontario, Canada. At UW I have been
            working with Douglas Stebila and Michele Mosca. I have been a research visitor
            at the lattice program of the Simons Institute at UC Berkeley in spring 2020
            and I interned at Microsoft Research, Redmond (US), during the summer 2019.
            Before, I was a post doctoral researcher in the Cryptography and computer
            algebra group at TU Darmstadt, Germany, where I received my Ph.D. in September
            2018 under the supervision of Johannes Buchmann from TU Darmstadt.
          </p>

